          "description": "I have had perhaps six (mostly cleaning) appointments with Dr. Kim over the past eighteen months and I like him and trust his opinion.  Impressively, he cleans my teeth himself (rather than have a hygienist).  He has been very thorough and knowledgeable in our discussions which I appreciate.  I am grateful that he correctly diagnosed an emergency condition I had a year ago that was solved with a round of antibiotics which took care of an unexpected Infection under a crown.  The last two times I was there he ran late by over thirty minutes and I asked the receptionist to consider calling or texting patients who are otherwise at work to let them know so that they do not sit in the office waiting to be seen when they could be working.  I have read the other comments below about the receptionist and I would just say that if you treat her with kindness and respect that she will do likewise.  In other words, treat others as you yourself would like to be treated...and remember, we all have bad days once in awhile; so be kind.",
