          "description": "I highly do not recommend this place, one of the receptionist there is probably one of the worst receptionist I\u2019ve ever encountered in my entire life. She is so disrespectful and unprofessional. Not only was she the same receptionist that told me they had a problem with verifying my specific insurance (mind you I work for the federal government for the past six years and my dental coverage is covered in all states) , she gave me an appointment that I had no knowledge of, while I was out the country, never told me that my insurance was verified until after I had to call my insurance and question why the listed provider that they gave me was claiming that something was wrong with my insurance, she never told me I even had an appointment. Then had me dismissed by Dr. Kim. When I asked to speak to Dr. Kim due to the fact that I have an opened root canal that he needed to put a cap on, she was very rude kept cutting me off and stating that he\u2019ll call me back. When I asked if he would be in the office the next day, she said no. When I asked if he would be in the office the following day she said no. Now Dr. Kim is in that practice almost every day so I know she\u2019s lying, so I will be coming to the office today June 3 and reporting her to Dr. Kim myself. I like the younger girl who is usually there she\u2019s more of respectful and kind and considerate, but the older Spanish looking female is so rude and disrespectful. Not only that, but they do not take you during your appointment time. Although Dr. Kim, is a good dentist, a lot of his staff will make you never wants to step foot here because of how unprofessional they speak to you . You still have to wait an excessive amount of time after your appointment due to the fact that they book 3 to 4 different appointments at the same slot. I\u2019m going there to not only report her but to be getting my medical records so I can go to a more professional dental Group. Go here at your own risk.",
